org.jetel.component

Class Dedup

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jetel.graph.GraphElement
      • org.jetel.graph.Node
        • org.jetel.component.Dedup
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Runnable, IGraphElement, CloverWorkerListener

    public class Dedup
extends Node

    Dedup Component

    Component:

    Name:

    		 Dedup

    Category:

    Description:

    		 Dedup (remove duplicate records) from sorted incoming records based on specified key.
    The key is name (or combination of names) of field(s) from input record. It keeps either First or Last record from the group based on the parameter {keep} specified. All duplicated records are rejected to the second optional port.

    Inputs:

    		 [0]- input records

    Outputs:

    		 [0]- result of deduplication
    [0]- all rejected records

    Comment:

    XML attributes:
    type"DEDUP"
    idcomponent identification
    dedupKeyfield names separated by :;| {colon, semicolon, pipe} or can be empty, then all records belong to one group
    keepone of "First|Last|Unique" {the fist letter is sufficient, if not defined, then First}
    equalNULL
    optional    		specifies whether two fields containing NULL values are considered equal. Default is TRUE.
    noDupRecord
    optional    		number of duplicate record to be written to out port. Default is 1.

    Example:

    <Node id="DISTINCT" type="DEDUP" dedupKey="Name" keep="First"/>
    Since:
    April 4, 2002

      • preExecute

        public void preExecute()
                throws ComponentNotReadyException
        Description copied from interface: IGraphElement
        This is also initialization method, which is invoked before each separate graph run. That is, it can be invoked multiple times. Use IGraphElement.firstRun() to determine whether given invocation is the first one. Contrary to the IGraphElement.init() procedure, this method should allocate only resources for this single graph run. All resources allocated in this method should be released in the IGraphElement.postExecute() method.
